## 2. Payment Reform and Delivery System Integration

Transitioning Medicaid from fee-for-service (FFS) to value-based payment (VBP) models is essential to incentivize cost-effective, high-quality care. Key reforms include bundled payments, accountable care organizations (ACOs), and alternative payment methodologies (APMs).

### 2.1 Bundled Payments

- **Definition**: Single payments covering all services during an episode of care, encouraging coordination and efficiency.
- **Evidence**: Systematic reviews show bundled payments reduce costs and maintain or improve quality, particularly in joint replacement surgeries ([Agarwal et al., 2020](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31905061/); [Struijs et al., 2020](https://doi.org/10.26099/936s-0y65)).
- **Implementation**: CMS’s Bundled Payments for Care Improvement (BPCI) initiative includes retrospective and prospective models, covering inpatient stays and post-acute care.
- **Benefits**:
  - Reduces fragmentation by aligning provider incentives.
  - Encourages evidence-based care pathways.
  - Demonstrated cost savings and quality improvements in multiple states and countries.

| Payment Model | Description | Risk Type | Services Covered | Example |
|---------------|-------------|-----------|------------------|---------|
| Retrospective Bundled Payment | Payments made after services, reconciled against target price | Shared risk | Hospital stay + post-acute care | BPCI Models 2 & 3 |
| Prospective Bundled Payment | Lump sum payment upfront for episode | Full provider risk | Hospital + physician services + readmissions | BPCI Model 4 |

### 2.2 Accountable Care Organizations (ACOs)

- **Concept**: Groups of providers jointly accountable for cost and quality of care for a defined population.
- **Medicare Experience**: Over 360 ACOs serve 5.3 million beneficiaries, generating $128 million in net savings ([CMS, 2014](https://www.cms.gov/Medicare/Medicare-Fee-for-Service-Payment/sharedsavingsprogram/index.html)).
- **Medicaid Application**: New York State’s Medicaid Payment Reform Roadmap aligns Medicaid and Medicare ACOs, promoting multi-payer integration and reducing administrative burden ([NYS DOH, 2015](https://www.health.ny.gov/health_care/medicaid/redesign/dsrip/)).

### 2.3 Alternative Payment Methodologies (APMs)

- **Definition**: Payment models that incentivize value over volume, including shared savings, downside risk, and capitation.
- **CMS Guidance**: Encourages states to adopt APMs consistent with Health Care Payment Learning and Action Network (HCP-LAN) framework to drive Medicaid VBC ([CMS, 2020](https://www.medicaid.gov/federal-policy-guidance/downloads/smd20003.pdf)).

