## 4. State-Level Examples and Lessons Learned

### 4.1 South Carolina

- **Focus**: Tobacco cessation.
- **Actions**:
  - Eliminated copays and prior authorizations for cessation services.
  - Standardized benefits across Medicaid managed care organizations.
  - Used federal funds to support Quitline counseling.
- **Outcomes**: Increased access and utilization of cessation services; recognized by American Lung Association ([CDC, 2016](https://nam.edu/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/CDCs-618-Initiative-Accelerating-Evidence-into-Action.pdf)).

### 4.2 New York

- **Focus**: Preventing unintended pregnancies.
- **Actions**:
  - Unbundled LARC payments from delivery services.
  - Educated providers to dispel myths about LARC.
  - Partnered with professional organizations to improve access.
- **Outcomes**: Increased LARC use and reduced unintended pregnancy rates ([CDC, 2016](https://nam.edu/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/CDCs-618-Initiative-Accelerating-Evidence-into-Action.pdf)).

